      "writtenOn": "2020-03-12T13:36:11Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This took me (a new person to this code) a while to figure out what was going on here. \"Tests should be straightforward enough to be \u0027obviously correct\u0027 upon inspection.\" [1]\n\nHere\u0027s a preliminary suggestion for how to make this easier to inspect.\n\ntwoStepsAndSleep :\u003d filepath.Join(tmp, \"script.sh\")\n...\n\neveryLineIsANewStep :\u003d func(sm *StepManager, line string)...})\ntimesOutAfter100Milliseconds :\u003d func(ctx context.Context) error {...\n  return Run(ctx, \".\", []string{twoStepsAndSleep} everyLineIsANewStep)\n}\n\nres :\u003d td.RunTestSteps(t, false, timesOutAfter100Milliseconds)\n\n\n[1] go/unit-test-practices#control-structures",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 90,
        "startChar": 58,
        "endLine": 97,
        "endChar": 3
      },
      "revId": "c11a659348b5094e9a3e45e1e63083308dcc4f3c",
